16 WHEREAS, Haven House continues to evolve to meet the needs of domestic violence
17 survivors, offering a safe and supportive environment for all family types with a family wing,
18 adult wing, large community rooms, and office spaces to enhance services; and
19 WHEREAS, in 2024, Haven House provided shelter to 695 survivors, processed 292
20 temporary protective orders, responded to 3,444 crisis calls, and delivered counseling
21 services to 432 individuals; and
22 WHEREAS, February 5, 2025, marks Stand With Survivors Day at the state capitol, a day
23 dedicated to raising awareness and advocating for the rights and safety of domestic violence
24 survivors; and
25 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable organization be
26 appropriately honored during this special time.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body recognize and commend Haven House for its many outstanding
29 contributions on behalf of those in need as well as extend sincere best wishes for continued
30 success.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
33 Haven House.
